w: Good King Wen-ces-las looked out | On the Feast of Ste-phen | When the snow lay round a-bout | Deep and crisp and e-ven | Bright-ly shone the moon that night | Though the frost was cru-el | When a poor man came in sight | Gath-er-ing win-ter fu-el |
